.playwright-mcp
# Exclude the broad scripts directory (Next.js / inspect / dev
# tooling that the runtime images don't need) but re-include the
# Cloud Run job CLI subdirectories explicitly. Each !-exception
# is paired with a Dockerfile that COPYs from that subdirectory:
#
#   - `!scripts/check-extensions` → Dockerfile.check-extensions
#   - `!scripts/migrate`          → Dockerfile.migrate
#
# Without the matching exception, the COPY fails with "file not
# found in build context" because Docker excludes the whole
# `scripts/` directory before the COPY runs. Listing each Cloud
# Run job's subdirectory as a separate narrow allowlist (rather
# than re-including all of `scripts/`) keeps the build context
# small and pins the failure surface to the directories the
# Dockerfiles actually consume.
scripts
!scripts/check-extensions
!scripts/migrate
